/><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-excerpt-tags\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"1\"/><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-excerpt-icon\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"32\">{\"displayOption\":\"top\",\"ids\":[]}</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-excerpt-images\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"35\">{\"displayOption\":\"top\",\"ids\":[172]}</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-routePath\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"27\">/blog/legend-behind-the-mix</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-headerImage\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"35\">{\"displayOption\":\"top\",\"ids\":[172]}</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-headerType\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"6\">medium</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-blocks-length\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"1\">6</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-blocks-type#0\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"10\">subheading</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-blocks-subheading#0\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"21\">Legend behind the Mix</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-blocks-background#0\" sv:type=\"Boolean\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"0\">0</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-blocks-type#1\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"4\">text</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-blocks-text#1\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"761\">&lt;p class=\"p1\"&gt;Ever thought&amp;nbsp;how your most loved songs are made? Ever thought&amp;nbsp;what process a song have to pass before the radio plays or you can buy the vinyl?&amp;nbsp;This trial of producing music is real art,&amp;nbsp;and in the background there are a lot of talented technicans working behind the scenes to achieve the tracks we love and enjoy and dance.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=\"p1\"&gt;We are enthusiastic about those technican engineers and got the oppurtunity to&amp;nbsp;sit down with our&amp;nbsp;legendary record producer and mix master James McMorrison. Together we talked about his growing experience over the years. The fast changing audio industry, his work with the band Civil Literature and what each sound board operator needs, to become a legend in recording.&lt;/p&gt;\n</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-blocks-background#1\" sv:type=\"Boolean\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"0\">0</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-blocks-type#2\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"5\">quote</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-blocks-quote#2\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"736\">First I started recording myself recording in the Bathroom, with whatever equipment I could find in the Walmart. Yees, I bought it from my little pocket money. When the time started, where I played in several bands, the technology started to develop. First I tried to record on the real stuff at that time - cassettes. Oh I was really into that. When I went to Liberty College of Music close to Nashville, I dreamed all the time about becoming a musican. A legend rocking the huge stages all around the world. But than the Liberty College started a new different program. I didn´t  realize it, but a friend told me. The program a good friend of mine recommended was called musc production and engineering. I never changed this till now</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-blocks-background#2\" sv:type=\"Boolean\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"0\">0</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-blocks-type#3\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"13\">media_gallery</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-blocks-medias#3\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"47\">{\"displayOption\":\"top\",\"ids\":[159,158,160,162]}</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-blocks-background#3\" sv:type=\"Boolean\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"0\">0</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-blocks-type#4\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"4\">text</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-blocks-text#4\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"1040\">&lt;p class=\"p1\"&gt;&lt;span style=\"line-height: 20.8px;\"&gt;I produced with a handful&amp;nbsp;people who inspired me. People like John Johnson, Mike Kuster, Norman Anderson, Chris Ride. Another guy is named Marc Honster who I just think is the Yoda of sound and production.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;Also, I invest profitably much time listening to the leading sound&amp;nbsp;producers and engineers of that time to become better and better. Particularly, I listened to Jarry McMarc, Conor July, Jeff Morrison , Mike Jazzman, Conny Rawls, Bobby Sherman, Jason Michael and Jeff Baldwin.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=\"p1\"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=\"p1\"&gt;I spent time listen&amp;nbsp;to their work, made&amp;nbsp;notes and gave my best to the same like they did. First I wrote down what I heard, what they did, later I tried the same in my songs. It was called an intense practice time. In the process of recreate of the sounds from the others I become better and better. I started to come up with my own stuff. I started to come up with my own things. I started to develop my own sound.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-blocks-background#4\" sv:type=\"Boolean\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"1\">1</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-blocks-type#5\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"5\">quote</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-blocks-quote#5\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"321\">One of the early Bands I produced, was Marshall Plan. I was sweading and shy when I produced them. At this time nobody have ever known this band. Today I still produce them. Each Record of them arose in the hands of mine. I love to see them - loving their music. My part is to give the best to make there passion audible.</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-blocks-background#5\" sv:type=\"Boolean\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"0\">0</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-articlesHeading\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"15\">Recent Articles</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-articlesBackground\" sv:type=\"Boolean\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"0\">0</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-articlesShow\" sv:type=\"Boolean\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"1\">1</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-template\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"4\">blog</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-state\" sv:type=\"Long\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"1\">2</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-published\" sv:type=\"Date\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"29\">2017-06-21T08:41:03.973+00:00</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-creator\" sv:type=\"Long\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"1\">1</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-changer\" sv:type=\"Long\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"1\">1</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"sulu:authored\" sv:type=\"Date\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"29\">2017-06-21T00:00:00.000+00:00</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"sulu:author\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"1\">1</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"sulu:created\" sv:type=\"Date\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"29\">2017-06-21T08:41:03.961+00:00</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"sulu:changed\" sv:type=\"Date\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"29\">2017-06-27T08:19:23.476+00:00</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-suluPages\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"140\">[{\"uuid\":\"7c2e7bee-163f-4e94-9c34-5813eef2d841\",\"title\":\"Legend behind the Mix\",\"routePath\":\"\\/blog\\/legend-behind-the-mix\",\"pageNumber\":1}]</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-suluRoutes\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"1\"/><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-blocks-quoteReference#2\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"18\">(James McMorrison)</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:en-blocks-quoteReference#5\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"18\">(James McMorrison)</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-title\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"33\">Eine Legende hinter dem Mischpult</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-seo-title\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"0\"></sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-seo-description\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"0\"></sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-seo-keywords\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"0\"></sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-seo-canonicalUrl\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"0\"></sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-seo-noIndex\" sv:type=\"Boolean\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"0\">0</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-seo-noFollow\" sv:type=\"Boolean\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"0\">0</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-seo-hideInSitemap\" sv:type=\"Boolean\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"0\">0</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-excerpt-description\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"133\">&lt;p&gt;Wir haben die Chance bekommen, ein Gespräch mit dem legendären Musikproduzenten und Mix-Master James McMorrison zu führen.&lt;/p&gt;\n</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-excerpt-categories\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"1\"/><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-excerpt-tags\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"1\"/><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-excerpt-icon\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"32\">{\"displayOption\":\"top\",\"ids\":[]}</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-excerpt-images\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"35\">{\"displayOption\":\"top\",\"ids\":[172]}</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-routePath\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"27\">/blog/legend-behind-the-mix</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-headerImage\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"35\">{\"displayOption\":\"top\",\"ids\":[172]}</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-headerType\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"6\">medium</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-blocks-length\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"1\">6</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-blocks-type#0\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"10\">subheading</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-blocks-subheading#0\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"33\">Eine Legende hinter dem Mischpult</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-blocks-background#0\" sv:type=\"Boolean\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"0\">0</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-blocks-type#1\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"4\">text</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-blocks-text#1\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"949\">&lt;p class=\"p1\"&gt;Hast du jemals darüber nachgedacht, wie deine lieblingssongs erstellt werden? Hast du dir schon einmal Gedanken darüber gemacht, welcher Prozess&amp;nbsp;ein Song durchmachen muss, bevor er Radiotauglich ist oder auf Schallplatte erhältlich ist? Musik zu Produzieren ist echte Kunst und im Hintergrund arbeiten&amp;nbsp;viele talentierte Techniker hinter den Kulissen um die Tracks zu erschaffen, zu denen wir alle tanzen können.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=\"p1\"&gt;Wir teilen unsere Beigeisterung mit diesen Ingenieuren und haben die Chance bekommen, ein Gespräch mit dem legendären Musikproduzenten und Mix-Master James McMorrison zu führen. Wir haben über seine Jahrelange und ständig&amp;nbsp;wachsende Erfahrung in der Szene, die rapiden Änderungen des Sounds in der Audioindustrie, seine Zusammenarbeit mit der Band Civil Literatur und&amp;nbsp;was jeder Sound-board Bediener braucht, um eine Legende in der Audio-Aufnahme zu werden geredet.&lt;/p&gt;\n</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-blocks-background#1\" sv:type=\"Boolean\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"0\">0</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-blocks-type#2\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"5\">quote</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-blocks-quote#2\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"851\">Ich fing damit an, mich im Bad selber aufzunehmen, mit Ausrüstung die ich für mein Taschengeld im Walmart finden konnte. In der Zeit in der ich in mehreren Bands gespielt hatte, fing auch die Technologie an sich zu weiterzuentwickeln. Als erstes habe ich versucht auf Kassetten aufzunehmen - welche zu dieser Zeit der Hit waren. Dort habe ich mich richtig ausgetobt. Als ich dann auf die Universität \'Liberty College of Music\' in der nähe von Nashville ging, träumte ich die ganze Zeit davon ein Musiker zu werden. Eine Legende, die die größten Bühnen rundum die Welt rockt. Doch dann startete die Universität ein neues, etwas anderes Programm. Ich wusste nichts davon bis mich ein Freund darauf Aufmerksam machte. Das Programm wurde \"music production and engineering\" genannt, also Musikproduktion. Damit habe ich bis heute nicht aufgehört.</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-blocks-quoteReference#2\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"18\">(James McMorrison)</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-blocks-background#2\" sv:type=\"Boolean\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"0\">0</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-blocks-type#3\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"13\">media_gallery</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-blocks-medias#3\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"47\">{\"displayOption\":\"top\",\"ids\":[159,158,160,162]}</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-blocks-background#3\" sv:type=\"Boolean\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"0\">0</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-blocks-type#4\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"4\">text</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-blocks-text#4\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"1049\">&lt;p class=\"p1\"&gt;Ich habe schon mit einer Hand voll Personen zusammengearbeiten, die mich inspirierten. Personen wie John Johnson, Mike Kuster, Norman Anderson, Chris Ride. Ein anderer heißt Marc Honster, von dem ich bis Heute denke, er wäre der Yoda von Sound und Musikproduktion. Ich investierte außerdem sehr viel Zeit mit dem Anhören von den führenden Sound Produzenten dieser Zeit, um besser und besser zu werden. Vorallem folgte ich Leuten wie Jarry McMarc, Conor July, Jeff Morrison , Mike Jazzman, Conny Rawls, Bobby Sherman, Jason Michael and Jeff Baldwin.&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=\"p1\"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=\"p1\"&gt;Ich verbrachte viel Zeit damit, ihre Werke anzuhören, Noten aufzuschreiben und versuchte mein Bestes, das selbe wie sie zu machen. Zuerst schrieb ich was ich gehört habe, was sie getan haben und danach habe ich das selbe mit meinen Songs versucht. Es war eine intensive Übungszeit. In dem Prozess in dem ich versuchte den Sound der anderen zu rekreieren, wurde ich besser und beser. Ich fing an, selbst auf neue Ideen zu kommen.&lt;/p&gt;\n</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-blocks-background#4\" sv:type=\"Boolean\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"1\">1</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-blocks-type#5\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"5\">quote</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-blocks-quote#5\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"389\">Eine der ersten Bands, für die ich Produzent war, war Marshall Plan. Damals war ich noch schüchtern und aufgeregt. Zu dieser Zeit kannte auch niemand diese Band. Heute bin ich immer noch ihr Produzent. Jede Aufnahme von Ihnen entstand durch meine Hände. Ich liebe es, wenn ich see treffe - ich liebe ihre Musik. Ich trage meinen Teil dazu bei, indem ich ihre Leidenschaft hörbar mache.</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-blocks-quoteReference#5\" sv:type=\"String\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"18\">(James McMorrison)</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-blocks-background#5\" sv:type=\"Boolean\" sv:multi-valued=\"0\"><sv:value length=\"0\">0</sv:value></sv:property><sv:property sv:name=\"i18n:de-articlesHeading\" s